A friend of mine received a gorgeous tarot deck for his birthday last November, and offered to do readings for all of us at his party. I asked the deck to tell me how my 2020 would go, and this is the reading I got.

I looked up the general meaning of each card, since Iâ€™m not as well versed in tarot as my friend. The reading has come true and it amazes me. 

Three of Stars- Through January and February I was seeing a psychiatrist and working on my mental illness (bipolar II and generalized anxiety disorder). Through some trial and error, we found the right medications and the right dosage. It was incredibly difficult to unlearn destructive coping mechanisms, but I improved little by little. At the same time, my workload at work ramped up, and I had to work harder than ever to make sure I didnâ€™t fall behind. 

Five of Swords- I started working from home in mid-March, to follow my stateâ€™s shelter-in-place order. Not being able to see my coworkers and friends had caused me to backslide a lot. A lot of my depressive symptoms returned and I was struggling. However, I discussed it with my psychiatrist and weâ€™re working towards improvement. 

Six of Stars- this part of my reading hasnâ€™t happened yet, but I know it will come. I look forward to whatâ€™s to come.

King of Cups- Despite my struggles and setbacks, the medication Iâ€™m on for my bipolar II and GAD have gives me a much more stable foundation to stand on. My anxiety is so much less now, and Iâ€™m not longer having hypomanic episodes. I know that as the year goes on, things will get better again, and Iâ€™ll end the year on a positive note. 

If anyone had an interpretation of my reading to add, please feel free!
